<mate-version>
  <platform>@MATE_PLATFORM@</platform>
  <minor>@MATE_MINOR@</minor>
  <micro>@MATE_MICRO@</micro>
  <distributor>@MATE_DISTRIBUTOR@</distributor>
  @MATE_DATE_COMMENT_START@<date>@MATE_DATE@</date>@MATE_DATE_COMMENT_END@
  <description>
    <!-- NOTE TO AUTHORS: Do not put anything in the following paragraphs that
    will be substituted by the configure script. Otherwise you will break
    the translations. -->
    <_p>MATE is a Free, usable, stable, accessible desktop
environment for the Unix-like family of operating systems.</_p>
    <_p>MATE includes most of what you see on your computer,
including the file manager, web browser, menus, and many
applications.</_p>
    <_p>MATE also includes a complete development platform for
applications programmers, allowing the creation of powerful and
complex applications.</_p>
    <_p>MATE's focus on usability and accessibility, regular release
cycle, and strong corporate backing make it unique among Free Software
desktops.</_p>
    <_p>MATE's greatest strength is our strong community. Virtually
anyone, with or without coding skills, can contribute to making MATE
better.</_p>
    <_p>Hundreds of people have contributed code to MATE since it was started
in 1997; many more have contributed in other important ways, including
translations, documentation, and quality assurance.</_p>
  </description>
</mate-version>
